  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. This package evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. The intended use scope—absolute hemolysis index prediction for pre-clinical regulatory submission supporting 510(k) clearance of a continuous-flow centrifugal VAD operating at 2400–3200 RPM and 4–6 L/min cardiac output—is described fully in the bound Requirement and Claim nodes. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors are assessed; 7 factors returned achieved levels meeting or exceeding required levels after corrective actions, and 6 factors remain at or below required levels but were accepted under the Minimal profile with documented rationale. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all primary input parameters. Decision: Accepted under Minimal profile review.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-class3-absolute-hemolyis-cfd-510k",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-centrifugal-pump-hemolysis-absolute-prediction-vad-conditions",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-generic-centrifugal-pump-cfd-hemolysis-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-experimental-dataset-2022",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-hemolysis-meas-dataset-2021",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/monte-carlo-uq-ensemble-10000-runs"
  ],
  "hasValidationResult": [
